The paper deals with mechanism design and revenue maximization for a combinatorial buyer, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The use of core-tail decomposition and subadditive valuations suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and optimization (cs.IT). The mention of additive and matroid constraints points towards artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and the study of approximation algorithms. Finally, the discussion of revenue monotonicity relates to economic theory and mechanism design (cs.EC).
